node.text:
Our Rifle Basics Class is available, for free, at TREX-ARMS.com.
Advanced shooting is all about mastering fundamentals and this 3 hour video captures Lucas breaking it down for a class of students. Check it out, take notes, and make a personal plan for improvement. This release also marks the launch of our new Training page, complete with a video archive of previous training videos, printable targets, drills, weapon and gear loadouts, and more.
And we're still just getting started...
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards #training

Eventually though, we all run into the problem of plateauing and that's where classes come in.

Candela is the measurement of directional light and is often a better way to determine what a flashlight is actually doing. High candela creates focused hot spots like on the @modlitesystems OKW and are very blinding and push light a really long way. When working inside though, that hot center can create a lot of shadows at whatever you are not lighting up. Options like the @surefire_llc M600 are often more flexible inside because of the "flood" of light that it throws. Though there are several great options for weapon lights on the market (Modlite, Surefire, Streamlight) finding what will work best given the environments you commonly find yourself in is crucial.
-

Move: Advance in the desired direction while staying safe.
Communicate: Keep your buddy up to date on what's going on and what you need.
-
Shooting is something we all strive to do well, moving and communicating are both done on a daily basis but can become complex when in gear and with radios. Still, they are all basic civilian tasks that should be practiced together. Keep it simple and execute cleanly.

Range estimation is a tool you can use for the rest of your life. Most people are taught to think in known distances like a football field. Visualizing 100 yards at a time is a lot easier than trying to see 400 in total. Start by paying attention to known distances. Capture what 200 yards looks like compared to 300. Next, get a range finder and make an educated guess before you use technology. ⁠
-⁠

Hot spots:⁠
From helmets to boots, our gear is often not custom. The designs may be quality but they are cut, built and finished for multiple sized users. If you have a small/medium helmet, you may still need to take time moving the pads around. Even once you get it comfortable, adding ear pro, lights, nods and counter weights can throw everything off, so don't be afraid to make adjustments to your gear on the fly.⁠
-⁠

To once again, prove that having a fancy rifle doesn't matter. If you suck, you suck. ⁠

node.text:
Most projects in life become more efficient if you do prep work. If you are going on a road trip, you may want to plan out locations for gas or bathroom breaks. Going camping for the weekend requires different food or gear plans depending on weather, amount of people or time gone. The range is no different. You will always get more out of your ammo and time if you plan ahead. You can either spend 15 minutes before you go or 15 minutes on the range. The reality is, range time is precious. Plan for success instead of showing up and hoping something good happens.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.text:
You dont have to be a pro distance shooter in order to be effective at range. The first step is knowing your holds. Barrel length, ammo and optic choice will determine some of the details on your holds. The AR platform is fairly consistent across the board, but as they say... "Close only counts with horseshoes and hand grenades." Spend some time on a ballistic calculator if you don't have a range with distance available. A simple app on your phone can do a lot for you if you're willing to put in the research time. ⁠
-⁠
Pictured here is a Vortex Razor HD 1-6 and yes, at the time of this posting, we have them in stock. ⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.text:
Why Glock? A few reasons. First, this is probably the most tested design over any other semi auto pistol. It has been proven and trusted all over the world by civilians, military and law enforcement. They also are offered at very competitive prices considering what you are buying. All of this has caused the Glock design to become very popular over the years. Today, the popularity of the gun means that magazines, upgraded sighting systems, holsters and parts are easy to source and well priced. There are plenty of other pistols out there, but Glock is one of the best choices you can make.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.text:
The concept of having one gun that does everything has become very popular over the years. The reality is, every choice you make on a build, has a trade off. Shorter barrels are easier to work with in confined spaces but have less muzzle velocity and reduced accuracy at distance. LPVOs help with PID and distance shots but aren't quite as versatile in confined spaces. No matter what you have right now, choose to be better with it today than you were yesterday. ⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards
